<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-76-0523 </DOCNO><TEXT>Two of the ways that investment bankers and brokers accomplish or aidthe financing of America's geothermal industry are by corporate financeand by merger and acquisition activities. Although corporate financeactivities, which generally have centered around project financings havebeen vigorous, the majority of the banking activities in the industryhave related to the acquisition of geothermal properties. Given the financialcondition of the industry, a sizable decline in corporate participationis anticipated over the next three years.</TEXT></DOC>